  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Tax Manager (Private Client Services)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<p><br>\nReporting to the Head of Tax and Tax Director, you will be leading a team of tax professionals to perform the following tax advisory and compliance services for our clients:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Preparing and / or reviewing of tax advisory reports</li>\n  <li>Assisting with the conceptualisation and implementation of various private wealth structures, comprising a mix of trusts, foundations, family offices</li>\n  <li>Handle and review tax compliance and advisory services to a varied portfolio of corporate, individual and trust clients</li>\n  <li>Preparation of proposals/presentations and assisting with business development and networking events</li>\n  <li>Performing tax research and analysis and preparation of marketing collaterals and thought leadership articles</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Qualified accountant or tax practitioner / advisor with experience working in a private client focused environment with exposure to a varied client base (e.g. High net worth individuals, family offices, trustees, asset managers)</li>\n  <li>A keen and insightful appreciation of the issues facing these clients and ability to seek out opportunities and deliver customised tax and non-tax solutions to meet their needs</li>\n  <li>Degree qualified with a minimum 6 years of relevant experience</li>\n  <li>Possessing an accreditation by SCTP will be an added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Candidates with over 6 years of managerial experience may be considered for the Associate Director position.</li>\n  <li>Strong communication, interpersonal and leadership skills</li>\n  <li>Excellent project management skills</li>\n  <li>Experience with Common Reporting Standard, Foreign Account Tax Compliance Act and Crypto-Asset Reporting Framework would be desirable but not mandatory.</li>\n</ul>",
